'''Ground mobile forces''' or '''GMF''' is a term used within the [[United States military]] that normally refers to communications units and their equipment. It is most often found in reference to [[satellite communications]], which has proven to be far more successful in rapid deployment of ground communications terminals than ground-to-ground terminals, due to the wide range of [[footprint (satellite)|satellite footprints]] and the relative ease of finding an unhindered [[line of sight]] due to a more vertical [[look angle]].

